      "locked": false
    },
    {
      "id": "YvWWPc1wgRxRIJo813d6C",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 530,
      "y": 798.2000274658203,
      "width": 478.735595703125,
      "height": 1040,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b02",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1660152643,
      "version": 128,
      "versionNonce": 1258117293,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1773913367945,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "OVERALL SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE\n\n\nCLIENT\n  Angular Frontend  →  Port 4200\n\n\nGATEWAY\n  Ocelot API Gateway  →  Port 5001\n  All Angular requests go through gateway only\n  No service is directly exposed to frontend\n\n\nROUTING TABLE (Gateway)\n  /gateway/auth/*          →  AuthService        (5003)\n  /gateway/user/*          →  UserService        (5005)\n  /gateway/wallet/*        →  WalletService      (5007)\n  /gateway/rewards/*       →  RewardsService     (5009)\n  /gateway/notification/*  →  NotificationService(5011)\n  /gateway/admin/*         →  AdminService       (5013)\n\n\nSERVICES AND DATABASES\n  AuthService         (5003)  →  AuthDB\n  UserService         (5005)  →  UserDB\n  WalletService       (5007)  →  WalletDB\n  RewardsService      (5009)  →  RewardsDB\n  NotificationService (5011)  →  NotificationDB\n  AdminService        (5013)  →  AdminDB\n\n\nEVENT-DRIVEN COMMUNICATION (RabbitMQ)\n  WalletService   publishes  →  WalletTopUpCompleted\n  WalletService   publishes  →  WalletTransferCompleted\n  RewardsService  consumes   →  WalletTopUpCompleted\n  RewardsService  publishes  →  PointsAwarded\n  NotificationService consumes → WalletTopUpCompleted\n  NotificationService consumes → PointsAwarded\n  NotificationService consumes → KycStatusChanged\n\n\nSERVICE TO SERVICE (HTTP - AdminService only)\n  AdminService  →  calls UserService  (fetch and update KYC)\n\n\nDESIGN PRINCIPLES\n  - Each service has its own isolated database\n  - No shared database between services\n  - Cross-DB relationships enforced at application level\n  - JWT validated independently by each service\n  - All client traffic enters only through API Gateway\n  - Async communication via RabbitMQ where possible",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "OVERALL SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE\n\n\nCLIENT\n  Angular Frontend  →  Port 4200\n\n\nGATEWAY\n  Ocelot API Gateway  →  Port 5001\n  All Angular requests go through gateway only\n  No service is directly exposed to frontend\n\n\nROUTING TABLE (Gateway)\n  /gateway/auth/*          →  AuthService        (5003)\n  /gateway/user/*          →  UserService        (5005)\n  /gateway/wallet/*        →  WalletService      (5007)\n  /gateway/rewards/*       →  RewardsService     (5009)\n  /gateway/notification/*  →  NotificationService(5011)\n  /gateway/admin/*         →  AdminService       (5013)\n\n\nSERVICES AND DATABASES\n  AuthService         (5003)  →  AuthDB\n  UserService         (5005)  →  UserDB\n  WalletService       (5007)  →  WalletDB\n  RewardsService      (5009)  →  RewardsDB\n  NotificationService (5011)  →  NotificationDB\n  AdminService        (5013)  →  AdminDB\n\n\nEVENT-DRIVEN COMMUNICATION (RabbitMQ)\n  WalletService   publishes  →  WalletTopUpCompleted\n  WalletService   publishes  →  WalletTransferCompleted\n  RewardsService  consumes   →  WalletTopUpCompleted\n  RewardsService  publishes  →  PointsAwarded\n  NotificationService consumes → WalletTopUpCompleted\n  NotificationService consumes → PointsAwarded\n  NotificationService consumes → KycStatusChanged\n\n\nSERVICE TO SERVICE (HTTP - AdminService only)\n  AdminService  →  calls UserService  (fetch and update KYC)\n\n\nDESIGN PRINCIPLES\n  - Each service has its own isolated database\n  - No shared database between services\n  - Cross-DB relationships enforced at application level\n  - JWT validated independently by each service\n  - All client traffic enters only through API Gateway\n  - Async communication via RabbitMQ where possible",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
